Load multiple data sources in parallel using async/await instead of sequential loading.

âťŚ Sequential (slow):
```javascript
model() {
  const users = await this.store.findAll('user');
  const posts = await this.store.findAll('post');
  return { users, posts };
}
```

âś… Parallel (fast):
```javascript
async model() {
  const [users, posts] = await Promise.all([
    this.store.findAll('user'),
    this.store.findAll('post')
  ]);
  return { users, posts };
}
```

This can provide 2-10Ă— improvement in route load times.

Cache model data in services to avoid redundant API calls on route transitions.

```javascript
// app/services/data-cache.js
import Service from '@ember/service';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';

export class DataCache extends Service {
  @tracked _users = null;
  @tracked _usersLoadedAt = null;

  async getUsers(maxAge = 60000) {
    if (this._users && Date.now() - this._usersLoadedAt < maxAge) {
      return this._users;
    }
    this._users = await fetch('/api/users').then(r => r.json());
    this._usersLoadedAt = Date.now();
    return this._users;
  }
}
```

Use Embroider instead of classic Ember CLI build for better tree-shaking, code-splitting, and faster builds.

```javascript
// ember-cli-build.js
const EmberApp = require('ember-cli/lib/broccoli/ember-app');
const { Webpack } = require('@embroider/webpack');

module.exports = function(defaults) {
  const app = new EmberApp(defaults, {});

  return require('@embroider/compat').compatBuild(app, Webpack, {
    staticAddonTestSupportTrees: true,
    staticAddonTrees: true,
    staticHelpers: true,
    staticModifiers: true,
    staticComponents: true,
    splitAtRoutes: ['admin', 'reports']
  });
};
```

Embroider enables modern bundling with Webpack/Vite, route-based code splitting, and significant bundle size reductions.

Always use Glimmer components instead of classic Ember components for better performance and simpler APIs.

âťŚ Classic component:
```javascript
import Component from '@ember/component';

export default Component.extend({
  tagName: 'div',
  classNames: ['my-component']
});
```

âś… Glimmer component:
```javascript
import Component from '@glimmer/component';

export class MyComponent extends Component {
  // No tagName, no classNames - use template
}
```

Glimmer components have no implicit wrapper element, are faster to render, and have a cleaner lifecycle.

Use @cached decorator for getters that perform expensive computations to avoid recalculating on every access.

âťŚ Recalculates every access:
```javascript
get sortedItems() {
  return this.args.items.slice().sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
}
```

âś… Cached computation:
```javascript
import { cached } from '@glimmer/tracking';

@cached
get sortedItems() {
  return this.args.items.slice().sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
}
```

@cached memoizes the result until tracked dependencies change.

Only use @tracked for properties that actually affect rendering. Over-tracking causes unnecessary re-renders.

âťŚ Over-tracking:
```javascript
@tracked internalCounter = 0; // Not used in template
@tracked lastApiCall = null;  // Not rendered
```

âś… Track only rendered state:
```javascript
@tracked items = [];          // Rendered in template
@tracked isLoading = false;   // Affects UI

// Non-tracked internal state
internalCounter = 0;
lastApiCall = null;
```

Use tracked-built-ins package for reactive arrays, maps, and sets instead of replacing entire collections.

```javascript
import { TrackedArray, TrackedMap } from 'tracked-built-ins';

export class TodoList extends Component {
  todos = new TrackedArray([]);
  tags = new TrackedMap();

  addTodo(todo) {
    this.todos.push(todo); // Reactivity built-in!
  }

  addTag(key, value) {
    this.tags.set(key, value); // Also reactive!
  }
}
```

This avoids the pattern of `this.items = [...this.items, newItem]` which creates new array instances.

Glimmer components should not use constructors. Use class field initializers instead.

âťŚ Using constructor:
```javascript
export class MyComponent extends Component {
  constructor() {
    super(...arguments);
    this.items = [];
  }
}
```

âś… Class field initializers:
```javascript
export class MyComponent extends Component {
  items = [];
}
```

Constructors in Glimmer components can cause issues with component lifecycle and args availability.

Follow consistent file naming conventions for components:

- Filenames: kebab-case (`user-profile.gts`)
- Class names: PascalCase without 'Component' suffix (`UserProfile`)
- Use named exports (not default exports)

âś… Correct:
```javascript
// app/components/user-profile.gts
import Component from '@glimmer/component';

export class UserProfile extends Component {
  <template>
    <div>{{@user.name}}</div>
  </template>
}
```

âťŚ Incorrect:
```javascript
// UserProfileComponent.js (wrong naming)
export default class UserProfileComponent extends Component {}
```

Use ember-a11y-testing for automated accessibility checks in your test suite.

```javascript
import { setupRenderingTest } from 'ember-qunit';
import { a11yAudit } from 'ember-a11y-testing/test-support';

module('Integration | Component | user-card', function(hooks) {
  setupRenderingTest(hooks);

  test('it passes a11y audit', async function(assert) {
    await render(hbs`<UserCard @user={{this.user}} />`);
    await a11yAudit();
    assert.ok(true, 'no a11y violations');
  });
});
```

This catches WCAG violations automatically during testing.

Announce route transitions to screen readers so users know navigation occurred.

Use ember-a11y or implement a route announcement service:

```javascript
// app/services/route-announcer.js
import Service from '@ember/service';
import { inject as service } from '@ember/service';

export class RouteAnnouncer extends Service {
  @service router;

  constructor() {
    super(...arguments);
    this.router.on('routeDidChange', this.announceRoute.bind(this));
  }

  announceRoute(transition) {
    const title = document.title;
    this.announce(`Navigated to ${title}`);
  }

  announce(message) {
    const el = document.getElementById('route-announcer');
    if (el) el.textContent = message;
  }
}
```

